        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Not sure if the ghouls in Neriak KOS to Erudite necromancers, as far as I know, I've never raised my Dead or their specific faction, and suddenly I'm amiable. However, paranoid necromancer = alive necromancer.</P><P>FP can get you about half of your spells, and Neriak has the other half. Paineel is horribly understocked :(</P><P>I find going through the East Freeport entrance (facing out of the gate to NRO, it's to your right in the wall, then mess around east and take the left fork) than dealing with those drowned ones.</P><P>Grobb will help you out with some spells which are almost research only, IE they are sold only in SK guilds, but maybe Neriak can help you also. I got someone to buy my spells in Grobb when I was little.</P><P>If you have friends who are higher level necromancers, get them to research for you, unless you really like to do it. It's a challenge and can be fun, but I couldn't be bothered, hence my skill is still erm ... 16, yeah. :)</P><P>If you have the words and are polite enough, most necros, assuming they have the skill, are happy enough to combine them for you if you go and see them with your book. A little donation for their services, as a token is often appreciated.</P><P>Probably for a high level necro, your 5 PP or so is chickenfeed, but well, they will appreciate the thought (and it's still port money). I know I always do, when some noob gives me an ale, or 3 gold because I bound them.</P><P>Saminga Amaranth, 60th Bad Girl of Avatars of Discord, Rodcet Nife.</P><P>Good girls go to Heaven, bad girls FD and /q out.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
